[lesson] Saved: [fixed] torch.OutOfMemoryError: CUDA out of memory. Tried to allocate 320.00 MiB. GPU 0 [lesson]   Solution: FIX_PLAN: In quantize.py:281-303, collapse the if model_free / else branches so the dense-model pre-load uses the same AutoConfig-only path (arch_name from cfg.architectures[0], model_type from cfg.model_type, moe from is_moe_config). AutoRound's own model load then runs with low_gpu_mem_usage=True and consumes layer-by-layer (~500MB-1GB per block on Mistral 23B), fitting in 32GB VRAM even at TUNING (iters=200).;SMOKE_TEST: python3 -c "import os; os.environ['HF_HUB_OFFLINE']='1'; os.environ['TRANSFORMERS_OFFLINE']='1'; from auto_round import AutoRound; from transformers import AutoConfig; from phases.quantize import is_moe_config; cfg = AutoConfig.from_pretrained('groxaxo/MagiSeek-Pro-V1', trust_remote_code=True); print('arch=', cfg.architectures[0], 'moe=', is_moe_config(cfg), 'expect_moe=False'); assert cfg.architectures[0] == 'MistralForCausalLM' and is_moe_config(cfg) == False";```;;--;
